    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Blood work\nElevated\ntroponin\n[7]\nElevated BNP\n[8]\nMarkers of inflammation such as ESR and CRP may be elevated, but are nonspecific\nElevated\nLFTs\nBlood gas to evaluate for systemic perfusion\nECG\nSinus tachycardia\nis most common abnormality\nOther abnormalities includes\n[9]\nLow voltage\nAxis deviation\nST or\nT wave changes\nAV blocks\nor conduction delays\nIschemic\npatterns\nSVT or ventricular arrhythmias\n[10]\nCXR\nNot sensitive, but often abnormal\n[11]\nCardiomegaly\nPulmonary edema\nPleural effusions\nEchocardiography\nUnnecessary if both CXR and ECG are normal, unless you have high clinical suspicion",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
